Krejcir, Czech Fugitive, Surrenders to South  African Police, Sapa Says

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-03-25T07:44:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/krejcir-czech-fugitive-surrenders-to-south-african-police-sapa-says.html
Radovan Krejcir, who is wanted by
Czech legal authorities, has handed himself over to South
African police, the South African Press Association said, citing
McIntosh Polela, a spokesman for the Hawks investigative unit.  Krejcir has been wanted by the police for the last few days
after Cyril Beeka, an alleged crime boss, was shot dead in a
drive-by shooting in  Cape Town , the Johannesburg-based  news
agency  said.  He is being kep’t at an undisclosed location and will
appear in court today on fraud charges, Polela said.  Assets including a Ferrari and a Lamborghini have been
seized from Krejcir’s Johannesburg home, Adrian Lackay, a
spokesman for the South African Revenue Services, said,
according to SAPA.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  